accessibility.text: Three degrees of theory separation
logo_RU_E_A4_CMYK.png
A. Scientific claim, either by construction, or by raising conjectures to principles:
Type of entity postulated (substance, structure, event, state, disposition, field)
Compositional, developmental, or efficient-causal connections between the entities in I
B. Tests of associations between entities
Signs of first derivatives of functional dynamic laws of connections in II
Signs of second derivatives of functional dynamic laws of connections in II
Signs of mixed second order partial derivatives (Fisher “interactions\") of connections in II
Ordering relationships among the derivatives in III, IV, V
C. Prediction of functional form and parameter values, tests of universality:
Function forms (e. g., linear? logarithmic? exponential?) of connections in II
Trans-situationality (Context relativity) of parameters in VII
Quantitative relations among parameters in VII
Numerical values of parameters in VII
